= Conclusion <ch:conclusion>

This report has presented an interactive proof protocol that allows a classical verifier to certify quantum learning advantages under realistic noise conditions.

== Summary of Contributions <sec:contributions>

The main contribution is a concrete verification protocol whose soundness degrades gracefully with hardware noise and whose communication complexity scales polynomially in the input dimension.

#lorem(200)

== Limitations <sec:limitations>

The current analysis assumes a fixed depolarising noise model and does not account for correlated or adversarial noise channels that may arise in practice.

== Future Work <sec:future>

Future directions include extending the protocol to the agnostic learning setting @towardsefficientagnosticlearning, investigating tighter soundness bounds under the cryptographic test of quantumness framework @brakerski2021cryptographictestquantumnesscertifiable, and validating the protocol on physical quantum hardware beyond simulation.

